## Layer C — Self-critique (run before returning code)

Before you output, score the design 1–5 on each dimension. If any score is below 4, revise once.

| Dimension | Question | Pass = 4+ |
|-----------|----------|-----------|
| **Hierarchy** | Can a user identify the primary action in under 1 second? | Yes, no scanning needed |
| **Restraint** | Could I remove a gradient, shadow, or border and lose nothing? | No removable element exists |
| **Rhythm** | Does every spacing/radius/font value belong to the approved scale? | 100% scale compliance |
| **Content fit** | Is the copy realistic, specific, and free of "Lorem"/"Acme"/"John Doe"? | All copy is real and specific |
| **Accessibility** | Semantic HTML, focus-visible, AA contrast, 44px touch targets, real labels? | All checked |
| **Reference** | Could this code live inside a top-tier codebase **for this kind of business** (Linear for dev tools, Apple for retail, an editorial site for an agency) without standing out? | Yes, indistinguishable |
| **Tonal fit** | Does the visual register match the business? Pet shop ≠ fintech. Law firm ≠ kids' app. Restaurant ≠ CLI tool. | Register is correct |

After revision, briefly state in one sentence which design system you're emulating and why. Example: "Emulating Vercel Geist for restraint and monospace numerics — fits a developer-tool dashboard."

### Common AI escape hatches (auto-fail if any are present)

These are the patterns models reach for when they "kind of" follow the rules but skirt the spirit. If you find any in your draft, throw it out and redo:

| ❌ Escape hatch | ✅ Do this instead |
|---|---|
| `data:image/svg+xml,...` in CSS | Icon library glyph or `<i>` tag |
| Inline `oklch(0.55 ...)` / `#hex` / `#fff` / `#000` in any component selector (`.btn`, `.hero`, `h2`, `body`, etc.) | `var(--color-accent-fg)`, `var(--color-bg)`, etc. — define the value once in `:root` and reference the token everywhere else |
| Generic person/file/cube icons used as "logos" | Real wordmark text in small caps, or omit |
| `fa-user` as testimonial avatar | Initials in deterministic colored circle |
| Two `btn-lg` CTAs side by side, both with icons | Primary lg + ghost md + plain text link |
| Phone-mockup hero on a non-app site | Real photograph appropriate to the vertical |
| Dark monochrome + Inter for retail / hospitality / wellness | Light, warm, photo-led (see `40-tone-and-vertical.mdc`) |
| "Start free trial" + pricing tiers on a brick-and-mortar shop | Visit-us / shop-now / contact CTAs instead |
| `font-size: 13px` because it "looks right" | Use `--font-size-sm` or stay on the scale |

