## When the user asks for "great", "OG", "premium", or "world-class" design

Pick the reference system that matches the **vertical**, not your default. See `[40-tone-and-vertical.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/40-tone-and-vertical.mdc)` for the mapping. Restraint is the signal of taste — but restraint applied to the wrong register is just blandness in the wrong key.

Common pairings:
- Dev tools, infra, fintech dashboards → Linear, Vercel Geist, shadcn/ui (often dark, monochromatic).
- Consumer SaaS, productivity → Apple HIG, shadcn/ui, Stripe (light by default).
- Retail, e-commerce, restaurants, pet shops, salons, cafes → Apple HIG or a custom warm palette, **always photo-led, always light by default**.
- Agency / portfolio / editorial → custom typography-led, image-heavy.
- Healthcare / wellness / clinics → soft, calm, light, often sage / cream / pale neutrals.

Do not default to gradients, glassmorphism, or "cyberpunk neon" unless explicitly requested.

